articles.description: Donte DiVincenzo scored a career-high 30 points, Jalen Brunson had 27 and No. 1 Villanova bounced back from its second loss of the season, rallying past Butler 86-75 Saturday.
articles.headline: DiVincenzo, Brunson, No. 1 Villanova rally past Butler 86-75

images.caption: Villanova's Donte DiVincenzo nails a jumper over a Butler defender, sealing a career-high scoring effort.
images.name: DiVincenzo racks up career-high 30 points

articles.description: Florida continued to solidify its postseason prospects with a 65-41 win over South Carolina on Saturday.
articles.headline: Florida rolls past South Carolina 65-41

images.caption: Chris Chiozza lobs it from the top of the key to Egor Koulechov for the finish.
images.name: Chiozza finds Koulechov for alley-oop

articles.description: Freshman Ivan Raut scored a season-high 25 points on 8-of-11 shooting, Will Tavares and Prokop Slanina each had a double-double and Fordham beat Duquesne 80-57 on Saturday for its first road victory of the season.
articles.headline: Raut scores career-high 25, Fordham beats Duquesne 80-57

articles.description: Roland Griffin scored 22 points and Iona heated up in the second half to defeat Saint Peter's 86-77 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Griffin has 22, Iona turns back Saint Peter's 86-77

articles.description: OSU gets a steal and Jeffrey Carroll slams it home on the other end before Jevon Carter's 3-point shot misses as Oklahoma State beats West Virginia 88-85.
articles.headline: Carroll seals Oklahoma State upset with thunderous dunk
